Sarawak Report is an investigative journalism online news resource that offers "an alternative vision of justice, transparency and a fairer future in Sarawak." It is based in London.
Sarawak Reportâ€™s website was blocked by Malaysia's internet regulatory body, Malaysian Communications and Multimedia Commission (MCMC), in the summer of 2015, approximately two weeks after the website started to reported on the 1Malaysia Development Berhad scandal. Sarawak Report continued to reach the Malaysian public through Medium.com, but that was also blocked in January 2016.
